content: Really enjoying it. It's a nice iteration from MechCom 3. If you enjoyed that, you'll enjoy this. The cube and new levels are worth the price üëå My only complaint is grouping. I wish pinch gestures controlled a box select instead of zoom level, which would give better control over selectingand grouping. Or even just adding a "Select onscreen units" button below "Select all" would work, so the viewport could act as box selecting.
needs moar unit & building types
Short and sweet, the best kind of mobile RTS.
Brilliant RTS game üëç
With improvements this could be a great offline game. Pretty good as is.
Multiplayer would make this game amazing. The controls and gameplay are stellar however it feels like a waste to only play against AI.
Cheap and ordinary. Though its good.
Finally a fun strategy game. Why don't you sell another 25 levels for $1 I'm sure that would be pretty quick to do.
Fun and not too complex

I wish there was a better way to make tank group. As how it is now the only way to make groups is to select all and add to group how about the 2nd group? basically the first group would be part of the 2nd group. Maybe multi select would be great.
Fun but custom 1v1 is too easy. I crushed the hardest difficulty on my 3rd game without doing the missions

super addictive game I have no feedback everything about ti is brilliant I just wish there were more vehicles and gamemodes. And 1 more thing why on medium after a while I had 2 refinery but they were only generating 1 dollar per 2 seconds plz fix cos otherwise its boring and u can't do anything.
Stuck on mission 23, but nevertheless nice game.
Very fun RTS, I have purchased the previous versions and see many similarities in mechanics and graphics. A second function with different graphics and mechanics would be nice.
Great gameplay, anyone familiar with the mechcom series, will feel right at home.
Pretty good for 1$ however needs to be expanded more

Ok i like this game so much but please add some nuclear missile, laser satelite, battleship, aircraft for more option because the game needs some kind of end game content to able to finish the game quickly. This is like my suggestion to you and keep it up. Create more games like this in the near future with a great game content unit, add more feature and option for the player who are really in love to real time strategy just like me..
Never found a game this good it has a good start but plenty of room to improve this wonderful game DEFINITELY WORTH A DOLLAR.
Cool game reminds me a lot of c & c the map and worlds could be bigger, more land space to explore
A few design flaws, not highly relatable, but definitely worth a dollar. Love the 3d world concept in an rts, it's pretty cool and well executed in this game.
It's great, lots of control over what type of units you output, and the maps are ussually pretty small for quickish games
Good game
eh.
Really cool for what it is if there where mp matches and perhaps different races even for vehicles and buildings to look according to the faction.
This is an amazing game. Great fun, one of the best RTS games available on Android. If you like Rusted Warfare you will love this.
Extremely repetitive, no replayability
Simple but satisfying great cheap rts for mobile
Cute little RTS with challenging levels, not so serious AI and interesting mechanics. Great job!
Simple, but well executed, and can be quite challenging in parts. Well done!
Well made interesting little RTS. Not much depth or replayability, but it's certainly with $1 USD.
You did it again. Cant wait for your future games.
Stuck at mission 10
The playfield is a cube so why am I forced to play in landscape?
A great game. Perfect mix of ease of play and difficulty, especially for a mobile game. Hours of entertainment. The appstore needs more games like this
Fun RTS, definitely worth a dollar. Would love multiplayer if development continues - would be willing to pay an extra dollar or so to play with friends :)
This is great, it's like MechCom with an interesting new world map system.
I'm a die-hard MechCom fan, so naturally I like this game as well. MechCom 4 baby!
